objenome.op

Class VariableNode<V>

  • java.lang.Object
    • objenome.op.Node
      • objenome.op.VariableNode<V>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Cloneable

    public class VariableNode<V>
extends Node
    The VariableNode class provides a wrapper for Variable objects. Each Node must only appear in one place in a tree, so to allow the same variable instance to be reused in multiple places, variables are not themselves nodes. Instead, a VariableNode wrapper is used. This allows the same variable object to be used in multiple locations within the same program tree while keeping the nodes unique.
    Since:
    2.0
    See Also:
    Variable

      • newInstance

        public VariableNode newInstance()
        Description copied from class: Node
        Constructs a new instance of this node-type. Rather than copying the node tree, this node is copied without children. In the case of many terminal nodes the bahaviour of this method will be the same as the clone method. By default this method will simply return a new instance of the same type in the same manner as clone, but with all children removed. Note that there is no requirement for an implementation to return a different instance.
        Overrides:
        newInstance in class Node
        Returns:
        a copy of this Node with all children removed
